# Commit and push

When finishing a change in this repository, always create a git commit and push
it to `origin` unless the user explicitly says not to.

- Follow the repository commit-message style and the usual git safety rules
  (no force push to main, no amending pushed commits, no secrets).
- Exclude host-local noise such as `ssh/.ssh/known_hosts` unless asked.
- After pushing, report the commit short SHA.
